DESERET GENERATION & TRANSMISSION CO-OPERATIVE, INC.
MARKET BASED RATE TARIFF
1. Availability. Deseret Generation & Transmission Co-operative (“Deseret”) makes electric energy and/or capacity available under this Rate Schedule for wholesale sales to purchasers with which Deseret has contracted.
2. Applicability. This rate schedule is applicable to all sales of electric energy and/or capacity by Deseret at market-based rates under the authority granted by the Commission on May 27, 1999.
3. Rates. All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchasers and Deseret.
4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions of sales shall be established by agreement between purchaser and Deseret.
5. Effective Date. This Rate Schedule is Effective on and after April 16, 1999.
6. Compliance with the Regulations of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. Deseret shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission imposes in its orders concerning Deseret’s market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission authorizes Deseret to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Deseret’s market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission concerning Deseret’s market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Tariff.
7. Category 2 Seller. Deseret is a Category 2 Seller in the Northwest region and a Category 1 Seller in all other regions as defined in 18 C.F.R. § 35.36(a).
8. Limitation on Deseret’s Market-Based Rate Authority. Deseret’s market-based rate authority is not limited and Deseret has not obtained any waivers or exemptions of the Commission’s regulations.
